  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Front Of House Staff",
  "description": "<h2>Front of House Staff</h2><p><strong>Company:</strong> FSA Holdings Pte Ltd<br /><strong>Location:</strong> Pickle Padel Movement @ Woodleigh<br /><strong>Employment Type:</strong> Casual / Part-time / Full-time</p><h3>About Us</h3><p>FSA Holdings Pte Ltd is a dynamic sports facilities and programs company specialising in <strong>pickleball and padel tennis</strong>. We run modern courts, coaching programs, leagues, tournaments, and social events, creating a welcoming space for players of all ages and skill levels.</p><p>We’re growing fast and are looking for enthusiastic <strong>Front of House Staff</strong> to be the friendly face of our facilities.</p><h3>The Role</h3><p>As a Front of House team member, you’ll be the first point of contact for our customers—creating a positive, energetic experience from the moment they walk through the door. You’ll help keep daily operations running smoothly while building strong relationships with our community.</p><h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><ul><li><p>Greet members and guests with a friendly, professional attitude</p></li><li><p>Check in players, manage bookings, and assist with enquiries</p></li><li><p>Handle payments, memberships, and retail sales</p></li><li><p>Support court operations and program schedules</p></li><li><p>Assist during events, leagues, and tournaments</p></li><li><p>Maintain a clean, organised, and welcoming front-of-house area</p></li><li><p>Promote programs, coaching, and upcoming events</p></li></ul><h3>What We’re Looking For</h3><ul><li><p>Positive attitude and excellent customer service skills</p></li><li><p>Strong communication and people skills</p></li><li><p>Reliable, punctual, and well-presented</p></li><li><p>Comfortable working in a fast-paced environment</p></li><li><p>Ability to work evenings and weekends</p></li><li><p>Experience in customer service, hospitality, or sport is an advantage (but not required)</p></li><li><p>Interest in sport—pickleball or padel experience is a bonus!</p></li></ul><h3>What We Offer</h3><ul><li><p>A fun, active, and social work environment</p></li><li><p>Flexible hours to suit study or other commitments</p></li><li><p>On-the-job training and support</p></li><li><p>Free or discounted access to courts and programs</p></li><li><p>Opportunity to grow within a fast-growing sports company</p></li></ul><h3>How to Apply</h3><p>Please send your CV and a short introduction to <strong>hello@picklepadelmovement.com</strong> with the subject line <em>Front of House Application</em>.</p>",
